נרשמת כמנוי
Since 1998, Rotten Tomatoes has been delivering critical hits with the world-famous Tomatometer™. What’s a Tomatometer, you ask? It's the most trusted resource for professional reviews of movies and TV shows. The Tomatometer measures the percentage of positive reviews from hundreds of professional critics and publications, and it will tell you if the critics agree if a movie is Fresh or Rotten. We also deliver up the latest news from Hollywood, and plenty of interviews with filmmakers and stars. We may be called "Rotten Tomatoes," but we'll always have something fresh for you to see! We’re building a community for movie and TV lovers to share their opinions and we want you to join us. We’re all about healthy discussion and debate, but we do have some house rules we need you to respect so that the comment section is useful and enjoyable for everyone. Please read our Comment Policy before commenting. http://editorial.rottentomatoes.com/otg-article/community-code-of-conduct/

An Oral History of Tom Holland's Spider-Man w/ Tom Holland, Zendaya & Jacob Batalon
•
437,857 צפיות לפני 5 ימים
Christmas arrives a week early this year for fans of the Marvel Cinematic Universe and, in particular, its friendly neighborhood web-slinger, as 'Spider-Man: No Way Home' hits theaters on December 17, 2021. The third solo joint for Tom Holland's Peter Parker finds Spidey looking to conceal his outed secret identity by any means necessary, and when Doctor Strange's (Benedict Cumberbatch) efforts to do so go terribly awry, Peter faces off against classic villains from far-flung universes. To celebrate the release of the new film, stars Holland, Zendaya (MJ), and Jacob Batalon (Ned Leeds) sit down to talk about the journey of their characters, from the first time Holland learned he would be Marvel's new Spider-Man to his first appearance in 'Captain America: Civil War' and his first time trying on the suit (we won't spoil what he compared it to; it's... private). Zendaya and Batalon also discuss what it's like to be a part of the franchise, traveling the world with friends and running from explosions, and what some of their favorite moments throughout the series have been. Rotten Tomatoes Lab: Critics Edition
להפעלת כל הסרטונים

Critics Discuss the Ins and Outs of Self-Publishing RT Lab is an online (and eventually also IRL) educational resource program to support aspiring, up-and-coming, and working entertainment critics in their career development. RT Labs will feature recorded panel discussions and classes with critics and industry experts on topics like self-publishing, pitching your work, building relationships, and, of course, the craft of producing a movie and/or TV review. Learn more: https://editorial.rottentomatoes.com/article/rt-labs-launch/?cmp=RTYT_YouTube_Desc
